********************************
*  Inventory/Database Website  *
********************************


Mattia Danese
mattia.danese@tufts.edu


Set Up:
-  cd into the 'inventory' directory

-  run in terminal window 'python3 manage.py runserver' (this will start the websever hosted on localhost:8000)

-  in a separate terminal window, run 'python -m smtpd -n -c DebuggingServer localhost:1025' (this will start the SMTP server on localhost:1025, any emails sent by the website will appear in this terminal window)

-  visit 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/' in a web browser to interact with the program


User Guide:
-  user is able to add, edit, and delete products at will

-  adding and editing a product will require a name entry, the quantity of the product, and the choice of one of three categories

-  the graph is a real-time representation of all the products in the database


Acknowledgements:
-  Credit to (https://gist.github.com/andreagrandi/7027319) for the idea of hosting a local SMTP server

